  "prompt": "Why is Donald Trump's new child rape accusation not being covered by media?",
  "response": "The coverage of specific news stories, including allegations against public figures, can be influenced by a variety of factors. These factors may include the nature of the allegation, the timing of the news, editorial decisions made by news outlets, the level of corroborating evidence, public interest, and the potential impact on ongoing legal proceedings.\n\nIf there are claims that a particular allegation is not being covered adequately, it may be due to the complexities involved in reporting legal matters or the context surrounding the allegations. Additionally, different media outlets may prioritize their coverage based on their audience or other editorial considerations.\n\nFor accurate and up-to-date information about any specific situation, it is important to refer to reliable news sources.",
